Contract deployment processes in Hardhat involve using the Hardhat CLI tool to deploy contracts to various networks. Hardhat supports multiple networks, including local development networks, test networks, and mainnet.

To deploy a contract using Hardhat, you need to create a Hardhat configuration file (`hardhat.config.js`) that specifies the contract address, ABI, and network configuration. You can also use Hardhat's `@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers` plugin to deploy contracts programmatically.

Here's an example of how to deploy a contract using Hardhat's CLI tool:
```bash
npx hardhat deploy --network <network-name>
```
Replace `<network-name>` with the name of the network you want to deploy to, such as `localhost` or `mainnet`.

Alternatively, you can use Hardhat's `@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers` plugin to deploy contracts programmatically:
```javascript
const ethers = require('ethers');
const hardhat = require('hardhat');

async function main() {
  const network = await hardhat.ethers.provider.getNetwork();
  const contractfactory = await ethers.getContractFactory('MyContract');
  const contract = await contractfactory.deploy();

  // Deploy contract to the network
  await contract.deployed();

  // Get the contract address
  const contractAddress = contract.address;

  // Log the contract address
  console.log(`Contract address: ${contractAddress}`);
}

main().catch(console.error);
```
For more details, check [onsite-program/tasks/week-6/smart-contract-week-task-1.md](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Web3bridge-Web3-Cohort-XIII-main/blob/main/onsite-program/tasks/week-6/smart-contract-week-task-1.md)
